The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Ondo State has expressed sadness over Saturday’s bomb explosion at Eleyewo in Akure North Local Government Area. A statement on Sunday by the Publicity Secretary, Alex Kalejaiye, commiserated with victims of the explosion. It hailed the government’s quick response, security agencies for allaying fears and seeking alternative routes to the damaged Akure-Owo road. The party called on companies and individuals to be more circumspect in taking precautions when moving such items. It wished the injured speedy recovery, and called on the Federal Government to expedite action on rebuilding the road. The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), in a statement by its spokesman, Zadok Akintoye, called on the Federal Government to help the victims to enable them cope with their losses. It said the explosion should be investigated to ascertain the cause, with a view to mitigating a recurrence. Akintoye also urged the state government to provide financial support for people who lost their houses.